  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Grant Aid in Response to the Volcanic Eruption in the Saint Vincent and the Grenadines</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On 9 April 2021, after months of heightened activity, La Soufri&#xE8;re volcano erupted on Saint Vincent and the Grenadines (SVG). As of 14 May 2021, National Emergency Management organization (NEMO) reported that approximately 24,419 persons from 21 communities were displaced through mandatory evacuation of the red and orange zones to the green zone. Initially 19,989 persons resided in private homes and 4,430 in the 84 government managed emergency shelters. This project is supporting the Government of SVG&#x2019;s efforts in the temporary relocation of persons internally displaced by the La Soufri&#xE8;re volcano eruption through strengthening the operational capacities of the NEMO to relocate the affected families to emergency shelters where they can stay till durable housing solutions are found.</narrative>
  </description>
